      • setForceReadTimeout

        public final BleNotify setForceReadTimeout​(Interval timeout)
        This allows you to set a forced read, simulating a notification. This can be useful if you want data back from a characteristic on a consistent schedule. If the interval given here is passed before another notification is received, a read will be performed.

      • getForceReadTimeout

        public final Interval getForceReadTimeout()
        Get the forced read timeout set in this BleNotify.

      • setNotificationListener

        public final BleNotify setNotificationListener​(NotificationListener listener)
        Set a NotificationListener for this BleNotify. This listener will only be called when toggling notifications/indications on/off. Use BleDevice.setListener_Notification(NotificationListener) to listen for incoming notifications.

      • getNotificationListener

        public final NotificationListener getNotificationListener()
        Get the NotificationListener set in this instance of BleNotify.
